[assistant] Fixed the `io.vertx:vertx-core:5.0.5` native test failure by updating:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `metadata/io.vertx/vertx-core/index.json`
[assistant] 
[assistant] The failures were caused by the index pointing `5.0.5` at a new `metadata-version` (`5.0.5`) with no corresponding reachability metadata directory, so the native test ran without the existing Vert.x metadata needed for:
[assistant] - `RegistrationInfo` reflective no-arg construction
[assistant] - `SerializableUtils` JDK serialization classes
[assistant] - `META-INF/vertx/vertx-version.txt` resource access
[assistant] 
[assistant] I changed the index so `5.0.5` reuses the existing `5.0.4` metadata bucket and marked that bucket as latest:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```json
[assistant] "metadata-version" : "5.0.4",
[assistant] "tested-versions" : [
[assistant]   "5.0.4",
[assistant]   "5.0.5"
[assistant] ]
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] No test sources or reachability metadata files were modified. I did not run the Gradle tests, per instruction.
